description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for dynamic enthusiastic Band 4 Nursing Associates nurses to work at the University Hospital of Leicester (UHL) across a variety of specialties on our inpatient wards. We actively encourage training and development for all staff and have a variety of opportunities available. The teams and environments will ensure a wealth of experience can be gained and provides staff with an excellent opportunity to develop acute nursing skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition all specialties benefit from established multidisciplinary team including medical staff, occupational therapists and physiotherapists, providing specialist knowledge and input to ensure we provide the best outcomes for our patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our aim is to provide a caring compassionate environment for all our patients and families. Therefore, we are looking for dynamic nurses with excellent communication skills who are motivated to provide a high standard of nursing care. Whether you have an desire to care for the older person, children or ambitions to work in a chosen specialty and the ability and drive to work under pressure, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Debbie McBride, Assistant Chief Nurse - debbie.mcbride@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
